WEBVTT

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:01.480
Alright!

00:00:01.880 --> 00:00:05.160
Let's give your app a real domain with automatic TLS

00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:07.720
. Four short steps and you're on the internet.

00:00:08.614 --> 00:00:11.574
Here is the path. Grab a Cloudflare API

00:00:11.574 --> 00:00:14.694
token, configure the infrastructure on the CLI

00:00:15.094 --> 00:00:18.134
, push it to the server, then deploy a Traefik proxy

00:00:18.134 --> 00:00:20.374
that handles DNS and certificates for you.

00:00:21.349 --> 00:00:24.309
First, open the Cloudflare dashboard in your browser

00:00:24.709 --> 00:00:27.589
. Go to My Profile, then API Tokens, and

00:00:27.589 --> 00:00:30.309
create a token with Zone DNS Edit permission

00:00:30.549 --> 00:00:32.789
so the CLI can manage your records.

00:00:36.189 --> 00:00:38.989
Step two. We set the public IP, the

00:00:38.989 --> 00:00:41.709
base domain, the certificate email, and

00:00:41.709 --> 00:00:44.509
the Cloudflare API token from the command line

00:00:44.909 --> 00:00:47.709
. The cert email and the token are shared across all

00:00:47.709 --> 00:00:50.429
your machines, so you only set them once.

00:00:51.435 --> 00:00:53.595
Infrastructure recorded in your config.

00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:59.980
Let us confirm the infrastructure settings were stored

00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:03.340
. Public IP, base domain, certificate

00:01:03.340 --> 00:01:04.860
email, all visible.

00:01:06.739 --> 00:01:09.059
Settings stored. Ready to push to the server.

00:01:12.521 --> 00:01:15.081
Step three. Push the configuration to the

00:01:15.081 --> 00:01:17.721
server. This creates the DNS records

00:01:17.721 --> 00:01:20.441
on Cloudflare automatically and prepares

00:01:20.441 --> 00:01:21.881
the proxy configuration.

00:01:25.082 --> 00:01:27.722
Pushed. DNS records are being created

00:01:27.722 --> 00:01:28.602
on Cloudflare.

00:01:32.066 --> 00:01:34.946
Step four begins. Create a small repo

00:01:34.946 --> 00:01:37.666
named infra. This is where the proxy

00:01:37.666 --> 00:01:40.626
will live, isolated from the application repos.

00:01:44.059 --> 00:01:47.099
Infra repo created. Isolated from your app repos.

00:01:50.548 --> 00:01:53.108
Apply the proxy template. It carries Traefik

00:01:53.108 --> 00:01:55.828
plus the configuration for Let's Encrypt and Cloudflare

00:01:55.908 --> 00:01:58.148
DNS-01 challenges, ready to go.

00:02:00.609 --> 00:02:02.289
Traefik configuration in place.

00:02:05.685 --> 00:02:08.485
And bring the proxy up. Traefik discovers

00:02:08.485 --> 00:02:11.525
your containers automatically. TLS certificates

00:02:11.525 --> 00:02:14.165
come from Let's Encrypt automatically. Your

00:02:14.245 --> 00:02:17.525
app is now reachable on the internet over HTTPS.

00:02:17.727 --> 00:02:20.367
Proxy is live. TLS certificates

00:02:20.367 --> 00:02:21.647
will arrive automatically.

00:02:22.591 --> 00:02:25.311
And that's networking sorted! See

00:02:25.311 --> 00:02:26.351
you in the next one.
